      <formalpara>
        <title>Ensure DB2 Primary Keys (PKs) are not nullable</title>
        <para>The Visual Studio 2008 Entity Data Model (EDM) requires that all primary keys are
<emphasis>NOT</emphasis>

   Nullable, and will fail to generate an EDM if any are. Thus ensure any tables
to be used are defined as not nullable in the DB2 database schema before attempting to generate an EDM.
In the case of the DB2 sample database all tables are not nullable, thus this should not be
an issue in this case.
    </para>
      </formalpara>
